('"Después de convertirme en presidente, le pedí a algunos miembros de mi escolta que fuésemos a pasear por la ciudad. Tras el paseo, fuimos a almorzar a un restaurante. Nos sentamos en uno de los más céntricos, y cada uno de nosotros pidió lo que quiso. Después de un tiempo de espera apareció el camarero trayendo nuestros menús. Fue justo entonces cuando me di cuenta de que en la mesa que estaba justo frente a la nuestra, había un hombre solo, esperando ser atendido. Cuando fue servido, le dije a uno de mis soldados: ve a pedirle a ese señor que se una a nosotros. El soldado fue y le transmitió mi invitación. El hombre se levantó, cogió su plato y se sentó justo a mi lado. Mientras comía sus manos temblaban constantemente y no levantaba la cabeza de su comida. Cuando terminamos, se despidió de mí sin apenas mirarme, le di la mano y se marchó. El soldado me comentó: Madiva, ese hombre debía estar muy enfermo, ya que sus manos no paraban de temblar mientras comía. -¡No, en absoluto! La razón de su temblor es otra. Me miraron extrañados y les conté: -Ese hombre era el guardián de la cárcel donde yo estuve encerrado. A menudo, después de las torturas a las que me sometían, yo gritaba y lloraba pidiendo un poco de agua y él venía me humillaba, se reía de mí y en vez de darme agua, se orinaba en mi cabeza. Él no estaba enfermo, lo que estaba era asustado y temblaba quizás esperando que yo, ahora que soy presidente de Sudáfrica, lo mandase a encarcelar y le hiciese lo mismo que él me hizo, torturarlo y humillarlo. Pero yo no soy así, esa conducta no forma parte de mi carácter, ni de mi ética. Las mentes que buscan venganza destruyen los estados, mientras que las que buscan la reconciliación construyen naciones". Nelson Mandela Aplicable en todos los sentidos... ¡Muy grande, Mandela!', '"After I became president, I asked some of my escorts to go for a walk around town. After the walk, we went to have lunch at a restaurant. We sat in one of the most central, and each of us ordered what he wanted. After a while of waiting the waiter appeared bringing our menus. It was just then that I realized that at the table directly in front of us, there was a single man, waiting to be served. When it was served, I told one of my soldiers: go ask that gentleman to join us. The soldier went and conveyed my invitation. The man got up, took his plate and sat right next to me. As he ate his hands shook constantly and he would not lift his head from his food. When we finished, he said goodbye to me without even looking at me, I shook his hand and he left. The soldier told me: Madiva, that man must have been very sick, as his hands would not stop shaking while he ate. -Not at all! The reason for his trembling is another. They looked at me strangely and I told them: -That man was the guard of the jail where I was imprisoned. Often, after the torture they subjected me to, I would scream and cry asking for some water and he would humiliate me, laugh at me and instead of giving me water, he urinated on my head. He wasn\'t sick, what he was was scared and trembling, perhaps hoping that I, now that I am president of South Africa, would send him to jail and do the same thing to him that he did to me, torture and humiliate him. But I am not like that, that behavior is not part of my character, nor of my ethics. Minds that seek revenge destroy states, while those that seek reconciliation build nations." Nelson Mandela Applicable in every way... Very big, Mandela!', [('spa', 1.0)])

('"Durante uma tourada, o toureiro sentiu-se mal. Teve tonturas e precisou de se sentar. Antes que alguém interferisse, o touro - que tinha sido agredido pelo próprio toureiro ao longo desse "espectáculo" (que tanto entretém gente de fraca cultura e com falta de humanidade) - apiedou-se do homem, parou diante dele e, para surpresa geral, ficou simplesmente a olhar para ele. O touro, como que sentindo o sofrimento do toureiro, foi solidário e ficou ao lado dele, sem recorrer a qualquer tipo de violência. Observem que o touro já tinha recebido diversas farpas no torso. Resta a questão: afinal de contas, quem é o animal?" SE TAMBÉM ÉS CONTRA AS TOURADAS PARTILHA VAMOS CRIAR UM MOVIMENTO E ACABAR COM ISTO !', '"During a bullfight, the bullfighter felt sick. He felt dizzy and needed to sit down. Before anyone interfered, the bull - who had been attacked by the bullfighter himself during that "show" (which entertained people of poor culture and lacking in humanity) - took pity on the man, stopped in front of him and, to everyone\'s surprise, simply stared at him. The bull, as if sensing the bullfighter\'s suffering, was sympathetic and stayed by his side, without resorting to any kind of violence. Note that the bull had already received several barbs on the torso. The question remains: after all, who is the animal?" IF YOU\'RE AGAINST BULLFIGHTING TOO SHARE LET\'S CREATE A MOVEMENT AND END IT!', [('por', 1.0)])

('"El calentamiento global depende del motor meteorológico dominado por el poder del Sol. Las actividades humanas afectan al nivel del 5%: el 95% depende de fenómenos naturales vinculados al Sol. Atribuir el calentamiento global a las actividades humanas no tiene fundamento científico". "Greta Thunberg, no debería interrumpir sus estudios, como dijo que quería hacer" Antonino Zichichi, profesor emérito de física superior en la Universidad de Bolonia y autor de más de 1.100 trabajos científicos, incluidos siete descubrimientos, cinco inventos. Franco Fazzi', '"Global warming depends on the weather engine dominated by the power of the Sun. Human activities affect the 5% level: 95% depends on natural phenomena linked to the Sun. Attributing global warming to human activities has no scientific basis." "Greta Thunberg should not interrupt her studies, as she said she wanted to do" Antonino Zichichi, Professor Emeritus of Senior Physics at the University of Bologna and author of more than 1,100 scientific works, including seven discoveries, five inventions. Franco Fazzi', [('spa', 1.0)])

('"El corredor keniano Abel Mutai estaba a solo unos metros de la línea de meta, pero se confundió con las señales y se detuvo, pensando que había terminado la carrera. El español, Iván Fernández, estaba justo detrás de él y, al darse cuenta de lo que estaba pasando, comenzó a gritarle al keniano que siguiera corriendo. Mutai no sabía español y no entendía. Al darse cuenta de lo que estaba pasando, Fernández empujó a Mutai hacia la victoria. Un periodista le preguntó a Iván: "¿Por qué hiciste esto?" Iván respondió: "Mi sueño es que algún día podamos tener algún tipo de vida comunitaria en la que nos empujemos a nosotros mismos y también a otros a ganar". El reportero insistió "¿Pero por qué dejaste que ganara el keniano?" Iván respondió: "No lo dejé ganar, él iba a ganar. La carrera era suya". El reportero insistió y volvió a preguntar: "¡Pero podrías haber ganado!" Iván lo miró y respondió: "¿Pero cuál sería el mérito de mi victoria? ¿Cuál sería el honor de esta medalla? ¿Qué pensaría mi Madre de ella?" Los valores se transmiten de generación en generación. ¿Qué valores les enseñamos a nuestros hijos y cuánto inspiras a otros a ganar? La mayoría de nosotros aprovechamos las debilidades de las personas en lugar de ayudar a fortalecerlas. Ver menos', '"The Kenyan runner Abel Mutai was just a few meters from the finish line, but he got confused by the signs and stopped, thinking he had finished the race. The Spaniard, Iván Fernández, was right behind him and realizing of what was happening, he started yelling at the Kenyan to keep running.Mutai did not know Spanish and did not understand. Realizing what was happening, Fernandez pushed Mutai to victory. A journalist asked Ivan: "Why did you do this?" Ivan replied, "My dream is that one day we can have some kind of community life where we push ourselves and others to win." The reporter insisted "But why did you let the Kenyan win?" Ivan replied: "I didn\'t let him win, he was going to win. The race was his." The reporter insisted and asked again: "But you could have won!" Ivan looked at him and replied: "But what would be the merit of my victory? What would be the honor of this medal? What would my Mother think of it?" Values are passed down from generation to generation. What values do we teach our children and how much do you inspire others to win? Most of us take advantage of people\'s weaknesses instead of helping to strengthen them. See Less', [('spa', 1.0)])

Iván respondió: "Mi sueño es que algún día podamos tener algún tipo de vida comunitaria en la que nos empujemos a nosotros mismos y también a otros a ganar". El reportero insistió "¿Pero por qué dejaste que ganara el keniano?" Iván respondió: "No lo dejé ganar, él iba a ganar. La carrera era suya". El reportero insistió y volvió a preguntar: "¡Pero podrías haber ganado!" Iván lo miró y respondió: "¿Pero cuál sería el mérito de mi victoria? ¿Cuál sería el honor de esta medalla? ¿Qué pensaría mi madre de ella?" Los valores se transmiten de generación en generación. ¿Qué valores les enseñamos a nuestros hijos y cuánto inspiras a otros a ganar? La mayoría de nosotros aprovechamos las debilidades de las personas en lugar de ayudar a fortalecerlas. EN ESTE AÑO, QUEREMOS QUE GANEMOS TODOS; EMPUJAMOS UNO A OTRO HASTA LA LÍNEA FINAL. TODOS MERECEMOS LA VICTORIA." Fuente: Paramita', '"The Kenyan runner Abel Mutai was just a few meters from the finish line, but he got confused by the signs and stopped, thinking he had finished the race. The Spaniard, Iván Fernández, was right behind him and realizing of what was happening, he started yelling at the Kenyan to keep running.Mutai didn\'t know Spanish and didn\'t understand. Realizing what was happening, Fernandez pushed Mutai to victory. A journalist asked Ivan: "Why did you do this?" Ivan replied, "My dream is that one day we can have some kind of community life where we push ourselves and others to win." The reporter insisted "But why did you let the Kenyan win?" Ivan replied: "I didn\'t let him win, he was going to win. The race was his." The reporter insisted and asked again: "But you could have won!" Ivan looked at him and replied: "But what would be the merit of my victory? What would be the honor of this medal? What would my mother think of it?" Values are passed down from generation to generation. What values do we teach our children and how much do you inspire others to win? Most of us take advantage of people\'s weaknesses instead of helping to strengthen them. THIS YEAR, WE WANT EVERYONE TO WIN; WE PUSH EACH OTHER TO THE FINISH LINE. WE ALL DESERVE THE VICTORY." Font: paramita', [('spa', 1.0)])

('"El uso prolongado de la mascarilla produce hipoxia. Respirar una y otra vez aire exhalado se convierte en dióxido de carbono, por eso nos sentimos mareados. Esto intoxica al usuario y mucho más cuando debe movilizarse, realizar acciones de desplazamiento. Provoca malestar, pérdida de reflejos y de pensamiento consciente. Genera gran cansancio. Además, la carencia de oxígeno produce descomposición de la glucosa y la subida peligra del ácido láctico. Algunas personas manejan su auto con el tapabocas, eso es muy peligroso, porque, el aire viciado puede hacer perder el conocimiento al conductor. Lo recomendable es usarlo sólo si tienes a alguien enfrente o muy cercano, y es importante recordar levantarlo cada 10 minutos para seguir sintiéndote saludable. Es contraproducente para las personas que atienden 8 horas al público, pues se están intoxicando sin saberlo. ¡Todas las vidas son importantes.!" Que la prevención no te lleve a otro problema... usemos la mascarilla con conocimiento de causa .. Todo en la vida debe tener un equilibrio." Doy fé que es cierto. ⚘ R e s p i r e m o s !', '"Prolonged use of the mask produces hypoxia. Breathing exhaled air over and over again turns into carbon dioxide, which is why we feel dizzy. This intoxicates the user and much more when he must move, carry out displacement actions. It causes discomfort, loss of reflexes and conscious thought. It generates great fatigue. In addition, the lack of oxygen causes decomposition of glucose and the dangerous rise of lactic acid. Some people drive their car with a face mask, that is very dangerous, because the stale air can make the driver lose consciousness. It is recommended to use it only if you have someone in front or very close, and it is important to remember to pick it up every 10 minutes to continue feeling healthy. It is counterproductive for people who serve the public for 8 hours, because they are getting intoxicated without knowing it. All lives are important!" Don\'t let prevention lead to another problem... let\'s use the mask knowingly... Everything in life must have a balance." I believe it\'s true. ⚘ Let\'s breathe!', [('spa', 1.0)])

text: ('"Es gibt einen Plan in diesem Land, alle Männer, Frauen und Kinder zu versklaven. Bevor ich dieses hohe und ehrenwerte Amt verlasse, werde ich diesen Plan bloßstellen." ~ John F. Kennedy So der ehemalige Präsident der Vereinigten Staaten von Amerika, sieben Tage vor seiner Ermordung. In seiner Amtszeit während der Hochphase des Kalten Krieges fielen historische Ereignisse wie die Kubakrise, der Bau der Berliner Mauer, der Beginn der bemannten Raumfahrt, die Eskalation des Vietnamkriegs sowie die Zeit des zivilen Ungehorsams der afroamerikanischen Bürgerrechtsbewegung. Kennedy war Mitglied der Demokratischen Partei und der erste US-Präsident römisch-katholischer Konfession. Wegen seiner Jugend und seines Charismas verkörperte er für viele die Hoffnung auf eine Erneuerung der USA. Die Hintergründe seiner Ermordung 1963 sind bis heute umstritten.', '"There is a plan in this country to enslave every man, woman and child. Before I leave this high and honorable office, I will expose that plan." ~John F Kennedy So the former President of the United States of America, seven days before his assassination. Historical events such as the Cuban Missile Crisis, the construction of the Berlin Wall, the beginning of manned space flight, the escalation of the Vietnam War and the period of civil disobedience by the African American civil rights movement took place during his tenure during the height of the Cold War. Kennedy was a member of the Democratic Party and the first US President to be a Roman Catholic. Because of his youth and charisma, he embodied the hope of American renewal for many. The background to his murder in 1963 is still controversial today.', [('deu', 1.0)])

('"Esta increíble foto marca el final de la carrera de Torero Álvaro Múnera. Durante la corrida, el torero se derrumbó de remordimiento al darse cuenta de que el toro no peleaba a pesar de las torturas que le fueron infligidas. Aunque lo hirieron con los picadores, el toro nunca tuvó la intención de atacar al hombre. El torero Munera comenta ese momento de esta manera: ′ ′ Y de pronto miré al toro, tenía esa inocencia que todos los animales tienen en la mirada, y me miró como para rogarme que no pelee. Fué como un grito de justicia, muy dentro de mí. Lo describo como una oración, porque si uno confiesa, con suerte, será perdonado. Me sentí como la peor escoria del mundo ".', '"This incredible photo marks the end of Torero Álvaro Múnera\'s career. During the bullfight, the bullfighter collapsed in remorse upon realizing that the bull was not fighting despite the torture inflicted on him. Although he was injured by the picadors, the bull never intended to attack the man. The bullfighter Munera comments on that moment in this way: ′ ′ And suddenly I looked at the bull, he had that innocence that all animals have in his eyes, and he looked at me as if to beg me not to fight. It was like a cry for justice, deep inside me. I describe it as a prayer, because if you confess, hopefully you will be forgiven. I felt like the worst scum in the world."', [('spa', 1.0)])

('"FUE FÁCIL. COMO SIEMPRE" "- ¿Cómo lograste traer tantas almas al infierno en ese momento? - Con miedo. ¡Oh si! Una estrategia excelente, antigua pero siempre actual. - ¿Pero de qué tenían miedo? ¿Ser torturado? De las guerras? ¿Morirse de hambre? - No no. No. ¡Era el miedo a enfermarse! - Pero entonces no hubo nadie que se enfermó? - Sí, se enfermaron. - Nadie murio? - Sí, están muertos. - Entonces, ¿no había cura para esas enfermedades? - Si habia. - Entonces no entiendo ... - Como nadie le enseñó que la vida y la muerte eran eternas, pensaron que solo tenían una vida e intentaron conservarla, incluso a costa de perder todos los sentimientos más preciados (no se abrazaron, no se despidieron, no lo hicieron). tuvo contactos humanos durante días); se quedaron sin dinero (perdieron sus trabajos, se quedaron sin ahorros), pero se sintieron afortunados a pesar de todo. Perdieron su inteligencia (una vez que la prensa dijo una cosa, y al día siguiente dijo lo contrario, ¡pero creyeron todo!). Su libertad? No salieron de la casa, no fueron a visitar a sus familiares ... ¡era un campo de concentración con prisioneros voluntarios! ¡Ah ah ah! ) Aceptaron todo para prolongar su patética vida por solo un día. No sabían que Él, solo Él y es Él quien da la vida y la termina. Sucedió así, y fue fácil, como siempre ". Del libro ′ ′ Berlice\'s letters ′ ′ de Clive Staples Lewis, autor de Narnia Chronicle ". El libro fue publicado en 1942', '"IT WAS EASY. AS ALWAYS" "- How did you manage to bring so many souls to hell at that time? - Fearfully. Oh yeah! An excellent strategy, ancient but always current. - But what were they afraid of? be tortured? Of the wars? Starving? - Nerd. No. It was the fear of getting sick! - But then there was no one who got sick? - Yeah, they got sick. - No one died? - Yeah, they\'re dead. - So there was no cure for those diseases? - Yes, there was. - So I do not understand ... - Since no one taught them that life and death were eternal, they thought they only had one life and tried to preserve it, even at the cost of losing all the most precious feelings (they didn\'t hug, they didn\'t say goodbye, they didn\'t). had human contacts for days); they ran out of money (lost their jobs, ran out of savings), but they felt lucky nonetheless. They lost their intelligence (once the press said one thing, and the next day said the opposite, but they believed everything!). Your freedom? They did not leave the house, they did not go to visit their relatives ... it was a concentration camp with voluntary prisoners! oh oh oh! ) They accepted everything to prolong their pathetic life for just one day. They did not know that He, only He and it is He who gives life and ends it. It happened like that, and it was easy, like always." From the book ′ ′ Berlice\'s letters ′ ′ by Clive Staples Lewis, author of Narnia Chronicle." The book was published in 1942', [('spa', 1.0)])

text: ('"Há alguns anos, entrei numa estação de metrô em Estocolmo, a tão civilizada capital da tão primeiro-mundista Suécia, e notei que havia entre muitas catracas comuns uma de passagem livre. Questionei a vendedora de bilhetes o porquê daquela catraca permanentemente liberada, sem nenhum segurança por perto, e ela me explicou que era destinada às pessoas que por qualquer motivo não tivessem dinheiro para a passagem. Minha mente incrédula e cheia de jeitinhos brasileiros não conteve a pergunta óbvia (para nós!): e se a pessoa tiver dinheiro mas simplesmente quiser burlar a lei? Aqueles olhos suecos e azuis se espremeram num sorriso de pureza constrangedora – Mas por que ela faria isso?, me perguntou. Não lhe respondi. Comprei o bilhete, passei pela catraca e atrás de mim uma multidão que também havia pago por seus bilhetes. A catraca livre continuava vazia, tão vazia quanto minha alma brasileira – e envergonhada." Texto: (Décio Tadeu Orlandi, bacharel em Letras pela USP e mestre em Literatura pela UFG. Quem faz um país é o povo!', '"A few years ago, I walked into a metro station in Stockholm, the civilized capital of the very first-world Sweden, and I noticed that there was, among many common turnstiles, one with free passage. no security around, and she explained that it was intended for people who for whatever reason didn\'t have money for the ticket. My incredulous mind and full of Brazilian ways couldn\'t contain the obvious question (for us!): what if the person has money but simply want to break the law? Those Swedish blue eyes squeezed into a smile of embarrassing purity. “But why would she do that?” he asked me. I didn\'t answer him. I bought the ticket, went through the turnstile and behind me was a crowd that had also paid for their tickets. The free turnstile remained empty, as empty as my Brazilian soul – and ashamed." Text: (Décio Tadeu Orlandi, Bachelor of Arts from USP and Master of Literature from UFG. Who makes a country is the people!', [('por', 1.0)])

('"Há alguns anos, entrei numa estação de metrô em Estocolmo, a tão civilizada capital da tão primeiro-mundista Suécia, e notei que havia, entre muitas catracas normais e comuns, uma de passagem grátis livre. Questionei à vendedora de bilhetes o porquê daquela catraca permanentemente liberada, sem nenhum segurança por perto. Ela me explicou que aquela era destinada às pessoas que, por qualquer motivo, não tivessem dinheiro para o bilhete da passagem. Minha mente incrédula e cheia de jeitinhos brasileiros não conteve a pergunta óbvia (para nós!...): "-E se a pessoa tiver o dinheiro, mas simplesmente quiser burlar a lei?" Aqueles olhos suecos e de límpidos azuis se espremeram num sorriso de pureza constrangedora: "-Mas por que ela faria isso???", me perguntou. Não lhe respondi... Comprei o bilhete, passei pela catraca e, atrás de mim, uma multidão que também havia pago por seus bilhetes... A catraca livre continuava vazia, tão vazia quanto minha alma – e muito envergonhada..." Quem faz um país é o seu povo!!! Depoimento de um Professor da USP.', '"A few years ago, I walked into a metro station in Stockholm, the very civilized capital of very first-world Sweden, and I noticed that there was, among many normal and common turnstiles, one with a free ticket. I asked the ticket saleswoman why that turnstile was permanently released, with no security around. She explained to me that this one was intended for people who, for whatever reason, didn\'t have money for a ticket. My incredulous mind and full of Brazilian ways couldn\'t contain the obvious question (for us!...): "-What if the person has the money, but simply wants to break the law?" Those clear blue Swedish eyes squeezed into a smile of embarrassing purity: "-But why would she do that???", he asked me. I didn\'t answer him... I bought the ticket, went through the turnstile and, behind me, a crowd that had also paid for their tickets... The free turnstile remained empty, as empty as my soul - and very ashamed..." Who makes a country is its people!!! Testimony of a USP Professor.', [('por', 1.0)])

('"Je me marre... l\'appartement sur la photo est pompeusement appelé « Unité de Vie Familiale » et se situe dans la prison de Condé-sur-Sarthe. Dans ce lieu que ne renieraient pas de nombreux mal logés du pays, le terroriste Mickael Chiolo logeait avec sa compagne à nos frais. Mais tant de précarité ne doit pas être admissible pour un bandit. Insatisfait de son sort, il a attaqué deux surveillants au cri de « Allahou Akbar », à l\'aide d\'un couteau passé par un visiteur. Parce qu\'en plus, si vous ne le saviez pas, à l\'entrée d\'un parloir, on ne peut palper au corps un visiteur qu\'avec son consentement, alors qu\'on vous palpe, consentant ou pas, à l\'entrée d\'un match, d\'un concert, ou d\'une manif des Gilets Jaunes. En résumé, les terroristes ont des droits et les honnêtes gens des devoirs, peut-être bien même, celui de payer leurs bourreaux..." Pierre Duriot', '"I\'m laughing... the apartment in the photo is pompously called "Family Life Unit" and is located in the prison of Condé-sur-Sarthe. In this place that many poorly housed people in the country would not deny, the terrorist Mickael Chiolo was staying with his partner at our expense. But such precariousness should not be acceptable for a bandit. Dissatisfied with his fate, he attacked two supervisors with the cry of "Allahou Akbar", using a knife passed by a visitor. Because in addition, if you did not know it, at the entrance to a visiting room, you can only feel the body of a visitor with his consent, whereas you are being felt, with your consent or not, at the entrance to a match, a concert, or a demonstration of the Yellow Vests. In summary, terrorists have rights and honest people have duties, perhaps even to pay their executioners..." Pierre Duriot', [('fra', 1.0)])

('"Jose Masvidal Padres musulmanes \'Exigieron\' la retirada de la carne de cerdo de menús escolares, en la ciudad de durval en québec. Respuesta del alcalde de la localidad: " Los musulmanes deben entender que deben adaptarse a Canadá, a sus costumbres, sus tradiciones, a su modo de vida, porque fue el país que escogieron para emigrar. Tienen que entender que son ellos los que deben integrarse y aprender a vivir en Canadá. Necesitan entender que tienen que ser ellos los que cambien su estilo de vida, no los canadienses, que tan generosamente los acogieron. Deben entender que los canadienses no son racistas ni xenófobos. Nosotros aceptamos muchos inmigrantes, de muchos países con diferentes culturas y religiones, contradiciendo a muchos países musulmanes que no aceptan los inmigrantes no-musulmanes. Por esta razón, los canadienses no están dispuestos a renunciar a su identidad y de su cultura. Por último, tienen que entender que en Canadá, con sus raíces judeo-Cristianas, los árboles de navidad, iglesias y fiestas religiosas, la religión debe permanecer en el ámbito privado. El Municipio de durval tiene el derecho de rechazar cualquier concesiones al Islam y la sharia. Para los musulmanes, que no están de acuerdo con la cultura y religión canadiense y no se sienten cómodos en Canadá, hay 57 hermosos países musulmanes en todo el mundo, la mayoría de ellos sub poblados y listos para recibirlos con los brazos abiertos, de acuerdo con La Sharia. Si usted dejó su país para venir a Canadá, y no para un país musulmán, es porque usted ha considerado que la vida es mejor en Canadá que en otros lugares. Hagase usted mismo la pregunta, solo una vez: por qué es mejor aquí en Canadá que de dónde viene?\' [URL]', 'Jose Masvidal Muslim parents \'demanded\' the removal of pork from school menus, in the city of durval in quebec. Response from the local mayor: "Muslims must understand that they must adapt to Canada, its customs, its traditions, its way of life, because it was the country they chose to emigrate. They have to understand that they are the ones who must integrate and learn to live in Canada. They need to understand that they have to be the ones to change their lifestyle, not the Canadians who have so generously welcomed them. They must understand that Canadians are not racist or xenophobic. We accept many immigrants, from many countries with different cultures and religions, contradicting many Muslim countries that do not accept non-Muslim immigrants. For this reason, Canadians are unwilling to give up their identity and culture. Lastly, they need to understand that in Canada, with its Judeo-Christian roots, Christmas trees, churches and religious holidays, religion must remain private. Durval Municipality has the right to reject any concessions to Islam and Sharia law. For Muslims, who do not agree with Canadian culture and religion and do not feel comfortable in Canada, there are 57 beautiful Muslim countries around the world, most of them sub-populated and ready to welcome you with open arms, according with Sharia. If you left your country to come to Canada, and not to a Muslim country, it is because you have considered that life is better in Canada than in other places. Ask yourself the question, just once: why is it better here in Canada than where you come from?\' [URL]', [('spa', 1.0)])

ocr: [('XI. Several vaccine candidates are expected to induce the formation of humoral antibodies against spike proteins of SARS-CoV-2. Syncytin-1 (see Gallaher, B., "Response to nCoV2019 Against Backdrop of Endogenous Retroviruses" - [URL] against-backdrop-of-endogenous-retroviruses/396), which is derived from human endogenous retroviruses (HERV) and is responsible for the development of a placenta in mammals and humans and is therefore an essential prerequisite for a successful pregnancy, is also found in homologous form in the spike proteins of SARS viruses. There is no indication whether antibodies against spike proteins of SARS viruses would also act like anti-Syncytin-1 antibodies. However, if this were to be the case this would then also prevent the formation of a placenta which would result in vaccinated women essentially becoming infertile. To my knowledge, Pfizer/BioNTech has yet to release any samples of written materials provided to patients, so it is unclear what, if any, information regarding (potential) fertility-specific risks caused by antibodies is included. According to section 10.4.2 of the Pfizer/BioNTech trial protocol, a woman of childbearing potential (WOCBP) is eligible to participate if she is not pregnant or breastfeeding, and is using an acceptable contraceptive method as described in the trial protocol during the intervention period (for a minimum of 28 days after the last dose of study intervention). This means that it could take a relatively long time before a noticeable number of cases of post- vaccination infertility could be observed.', 'XI. Several vaccine candidates are expected to induce the formation of humoral antibodies against spike proteins of SARS-CoV-2. Syncytin-1 (see Gallaher, B., "Response to nCoV2019 Against Backdrop of Endogenous Retroviruses" - [URL] against-backdrop-of-endogenous-retroviruses/396), which is derived from human endogenous retroviruses (HERV) and is responsible for the development of a placenta in mammals and humans and is therefore an essential prerequisite for a successful pregnancy, is also found in homologous form in the spike proteins of SARS viruses. There is no indication whether antibodies against spike proteins of SARS viruses would also act like anti-Syncytin-1 antibodies. However, if this were to be the case this would then also prevent the formation of a placenta which would result in vaccinated women essentially becoming infertile. To my knowledge, Pfizer/BioNTech has yet to release any samples of written materials provided to patients, so it is unclear what, if any, information regarding (potential) fertility-specific risks caused by antibodies is included. According to section 10.4.2 of the Pfizer/BioNTech trial protocol, a woman of childbearing potential (WOCBP) is eligible to participate if she is not pregnant or breastfeeding, and is using an acceptable contraceptive method as described in the trial protocol during the intervention period (for a minimum of 28 days after the last dose of study intervention). This means that it could take a relatively long time before a noticeable number of cases of post- vaccination infertility could be observed.', [('eng', 1.0)])]
text: ('"L\'ancien responsable de la recherche respiratoire chez Pfizer, le Dr Yeadon, et le spécialiste des poumons et ancien chef du service de SP, le Dr Wodarg, ont déposé une pétition auprès de l\'AEM pour avertir que les vaccins COVID peuvent provoquer une STÉRILITÉ féminine" Vous trouverez ci-dessous le texte complet ainsi que la partie de la pétition Yeadon & Wodard qui explique comment les anticorps produits par le vaccin COVID pourraient rendre les femmes infertiles en attaquant une protéine nécessaire à la formation d\'un placenta. Ceci est le texte intégral de la pétition déposée par les Drs. Yeadon et Wodarg: [URL]', '"Former head of respiratory research at Pfizer, Dr. Yeadon, and lung specialist and former head of the MS department, Dr. Wodarg, have filed a petition with the WEA warning that COVID vaccines can cause feminine STERILITY" Below is the full text as well as the part of the Yeadon & Wodard petition that explains how antibodies produced by the COVID vaccine could render women infertile by attacking a protein necessary for the formation of a placenta. This is the full text of the petition filed by Drs. Yeadon and Wodarg: [URL]', [('fra', 1.0)])

text: ('"L\'utilisation prolongée du masque produit de l\'hypoxie. Hypoxie cérébrale concerne un faible approvisionnement en oxygène au cerveau. Respirer encore et encore l\'air exhalé devient du dioxyde de carbone, c\'est pourquoi nous sentons étourdissements. ('"La mujer de la foto es la directora del Banco Central de Londres. Antes de comenzar su primer día de trabajo, su padre le dijo: "No le digas a nadie que creciste en una familia pobre y que tu padre es limpiador de calles, todos tus compañeros se reirán de ti". Al día siguiente la mujer publicó esta foto en las redes sociales con el siguiente mensaje: "Crecí en una familia pobre y mi padre trabaja como barrendero… quiero agradecerle por su educación y por sus esfuerzos económicos durante el período de estudio. Te amo, papá. Eres mi orgullo".', '"The woman in the photo is the director of the Central Bank of London. Before starting his first day of work, his father told him: "Don\'t tell anyone that you grew up in a poor family and that your father is a street cleaner, all your colleagues will laugh at you." The next day the woman posted this photo on social media with the following message: "I grew up in a poor family and my father works as a sweeper... I want to thank him for his education and for his economic efforts during the study period. I love you, dad. You are my pride."', [('spa', 1.0)])

('"Los antiguos egipcios trataban a algunos pacientes comiendo pan mohoso, y nadie entendía por qué". "Hasta el año 1928, cinco mil años después, llegó la ciencia moderna y el científico Alexander Fleming descubría que la penicilina tenía un gran efecto como antibiótico en las bacterias". ¿Cuál es la relación del pan con el tema? "Cuando el pan se pudre, secreta un hongo llamado Penicillium, del cual se deriva la penicilina, el antibiótico más famoso usado hasta ahora para tratar algunos tipos de bacterias conocidas por los egipcios hace 5.000 años🍞', '"The ancient Egyptians treated some patients by eating moldy bread, and no one understood why." "Until the year 1928, five thousand years later, modern science arrived and the scientist Alexander Fleming discovered that penicillin had a great effect as an antibiotic on bacteria." What is the bread\'s relationship to the theme? "When bread rots, it secretes a fungus called Penicillium, from which penicillin is derived, the most famous antibiotic used so far to treat some types of bacteria. known by the Egyptians 5,000 years ago🍞', [('spa', 1.0)])

text: ('"Lucho contra tres gigantes, querido Sancho; estos son: el MIEDO, que tiene fuerte raigambre y que se apodera de los seres y los sujeta para que no vayan más allá del muro de lo socialmente permitido o admitido; el otro es la INJUSTICIA, que subyace en el mundo disfrazada de justicia general, pero que es una justicia instaurada por unos pocos para defender mezquinos y egoístas intereses; y el otro es la IGNORANCIA, que anda también vestida o disfrazada de conocimiento y que embauca a los seres para que crean saber cuando no saben en realidad y que crean estar en lo cierto cuando no lo están. Esta ignorancia, disfrazada de conocimiento, hace mucho daño, e impide a los seres ir más allá en la línea de conocer realmente y conocerse". *Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra / El Quijote de la Mancha', '"I am fighting against three giants, dear Sancho; these are: FEAR, which has strong roots and which seizes beings and holds them so that they do not go beyond the wall of what is socially permitted or admitted; the other is INJUSTICE, that underlies the world disguised as general justice, but that is a justice established by a few to defend petty and selfish interests; and the other is IGNORANCE, which is also dressed or disguised as knowledge and that tricks beings into believing to know when they do not really know and to believe they are right when they are not. This ignorance, disguised as knowledge, does a lot of damage, and prevents beings from going further in the line of really knowing and knowing themselves". *Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra / Don Quixote de la Mancha', [('spa', 1.0)])

ocr: [('AJ2780706 20 BANCO DE MEXICO 20 "Nomás le cae a la gente y lo guarda en su cartera"', 'AJ2780706 twenty BANK OF MEXICO twenty "It just falls to people and keep it in your wallet', [('spa', 0.7975755929946899)])]
text: ('"MAÑA" DE LOS MEXICANOS ESTÁ DEVORANDO LA ECONOMÍA FORMAL La Secretaría de Hacienda informó que a pesar de que ya están en circulación los nuevos billetes de $50 y de a $20, éstos no se ven en ningún lado de la economía formal o informal, ya que se presume las personas no quieren gastarlo debido a que quieren preservarlos. “Nomás ven un billete nuevo y lo guardan eternamente en su cartera”, explicó el titular de Hacienda como preámbulo a su explicación a la desaceleración económica. De acuerdo con las autoridades hacendarias, esta maña está afectando profundamente al país, y podría provocar que “la cuesta de enero” se sienta aún más pues llegará un punto en donde la gente tendrán que pagar todo con moneditas de a peso. El estancamiento de la economía sería por culpa de las personas que no sueltan su billete nuevo del ajolote, lo que ha provocando que el flujo de efectivo se detenga por completo. “Esto no hubiera pasado si el ajolote lo hubiéramos puesto en el billete de $1000”, se lamentó reflexivamente el secretario de hacienda. (Tomado de El Reporte Urbano)', '"TOMORROW" OF MEXICANS IS DEVOURING THE FORMAL ECONOMY The Ministry of Finance reported that despite the fact that the new $50 and $20 bills are already in circulation, they are not seen anywhere in the formal or informal economy, since it is presumed that people do not want to spend them because they want to preserve them. "They just see a new ticket and they keep it in their wallet forever," explained the head of the Treasury as a preamble to his explanation of the economic slowdown. According to the treasury authorities, this morning is deeply affecting the country, and could cause "the January cost" to be felt even more, since there will come a point where people will have to pay for everything with small pesos. The stagnation of the economy would be due to the people who do not drop their new axolotl bill, which has caused the cash flow to stop completely. “This would not have happened if we had put the axolotl on the $1,000 bill,” the treasury secretary thoughtfully lamented. (Taken from The Urban Report)', [('spa', 1.0)])
